OL,3,CExtinction Rebellion co-founder spared
OL,4,Cjail over conspiracy to close Heathrow
OL,6,FMichael Goold, defending Maxey, said
OL,7,Fthe defendant was "motivated by the
OL,8,Fsincere heartfelt concern, and
OL,9,Fjustified concern, about the climate
OL,10,Femergency."
OL,12,FJudge Martin Edmunds KC said the plan
OL,13,Fwas developed under the banner of
OL,14,FHeathrow Pause and there was evidence
OL,15,FExtinction Rebellion members chose not
OL,16,Fto become involved as they "valued
OL,17,Fplans to be too extreme."
OL,19,FHe added that the small number of
OL,20,Fdrones flown "did not cause any
OL,21,Fdisruption to flights."
